<h2 id="20">2. Currency conversion</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the <a href="/en/item/managing-items#870">Sales prices</a> menu, you activate the <strong>Currency: Live conversion</strong> option to convert the store currency into foreign currencies. Additionally, go to <strong>System » Orders » Payment » Currencies</strong> and configure the currency settings. To do so, proceed as described below.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Currency conversion:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Orders » Payment » Currencies</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings as desired. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-currency-settings">Table 2</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<table id="table-currency-settings" class="tableblock frame-all grid-all spread">
<caption class="title">Table 2. Currency settings</caption>
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 50%;">
<col style="width: 50%;">
</colgroup>
<thead>
<tr>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Setting</th>
<th class="tableblock halign-left valign-top">Explanation</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Standard currency</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Select a <a href="/en/order-processing/payment/currencies#30">system currency</a> from the drop-down list.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Automatically update conversion factors daily</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>This option specifies whether or not the conversion factors should automatically be updated on a daily basis.<br>
<strong>Yes</strong> = The conversion factors will automatically be updated overnight. Furthermore, a new option will appear directly below this field. The option is called <strong>Last automatic update</strong> (see next option).<br>
<strong>No</strong> = A <strong>reload icon</strong> will be displayed for each currency. This icon can be used to manually update the conversion factors any time.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Last automatic update</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>Display the last update of the conversion factors. This field is only visible if the option <strong>Automatically update conversion factors daily</strong> was set to <strong>Yes</strong>.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Conversion factor for standard currency into EUR, USD, CHF…​</strong></p>
</div></div></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div><div class="paragraph">
<p>When opening the menu, you will see that there are already exchange rates, but that they may need to be updated. Click on the <strong>reload icon</strong> to have the new exchange rate calculated. Alternatively, set the option <strong>Automatically update conversion factors daily</strong> to <strong>Yes</strong>.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
