<h2 id="30">3. Specifying the system currency</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you work with different currencies, then you will have to define one currency as the standard currency for the system. This currency is the default currency if no other is selected. The system’s standard currency is <strong>EUR</strong> (Euro).</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In plentymarkets, orders are always created in the standard currency. Each order shows which currency was selected by the customer. If an order was not made in the standard currency, then the current exchange rate is also saved with the order. These values can be used to analyse the order data any time or they can be used e.g. for automatic notifications.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Specifying the system currency:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Orders » Payment » Currencies</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a currency under <strong>Standard currency</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This setting is not necessarily identical to the currency <a href="/en/order-processing/payment/currencies#70">displayed in your online store</a>. A different standard currency can be defined for each store and language. Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » Online store » Currency</strong> to carry out this setting.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="40">4. Displaying the currency symbol in the order process</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Select whether currencies are to be displayed as ISO codes or as symbols in the online store. For example, euro would be displayed with the ISO code <strong>EUR</strong> or with the symbol <strong>€</strong>. This setting controls how the currency is displayed during the <strong>order process</strong> and in the <strong>My account</strong> area. <a href="/en/order-processing/payment/currencies#70">Template variables and functions</a> are used to display the currency in other areas of the online store.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Displaying the currency symbol in the order process:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » Online store » Currency</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the option <strong>Symbol</strong> from the <strong>Symbol</strong> drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="60">5. Specifying the standard currency for the online store</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you offer different languages for your online store, you can specify a standard currency for every language. If you work with several clients (stores), then you can carry out the settings for each store individually. If you want to carry out these settings for a different store, then replace the menu point <strong>Standard</strong> with the name of the store.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Specifying the standard currency for the online store:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » Online store » Currency</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a standard currency for each language of the online store under <strong>Standard currency</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="70">6. Customising the currency displayed in the online store</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can allow your customers to switch from one currency to another. This is useful, e.g. if you run a German store and you sell your items in Germany with the currency EUR and in Switzerland with the currency CHF. The following template functions make it possible to switch from one currency to another:</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>$Link_Currency(EUR)</strong><br>
<strong>$Link_Currency(CHF)</strong><br>
<strong>$Link_Currency(USD)</strong></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>These are inserted with the following codes:</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>&lt;a href="$Link_Currency(EUR)"&gt;EUR&lt;/a&gt;</strong><br>
<strong>&lt;a href="$Link_Currency(CHF)"&gt;CHF&lt;/a&gt;</strong><br>
<strong>&lt;a href="$Link_Currency(USD)"&gt;USD&lt;/a&gt;</strong></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Inserting template functions:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>CMS » Web design</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the folder <strong>Layout » PageDesign</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open a template, e.g. <strong>PageDesignContent</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Copy the desired code above and insert it into the desired location within the template.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Replace currency symbols</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you previously worked with currency symbols, then replace them with the template variable <strong>$Currency</strong>. This template variable represents the currency currently selected in the online store.</p>
</div>
